message: I had already created the dispute, you can check it for yourselves.

I don't know how many times it is necessary to clarify that she is also an author. In addition, it's important to have a short description of her awards in the first paragraph since each actor has it in their respective article.
She has also published two books, Brunette Ambition (2014) and You First: Journal Your Way to Your Best Life (2015).
It's fine if you want to put it in the 'public image' subheading, but this is irrelevant to the short description. Neither Brad Pitt nor Elvis himself have that 'appellation' in their description.

* Author: "Michele has also published two books, Brunette Ambition (2014) and You First: Journal Your Way to Your Best Life (2015)." * Songwriter: She also writes songs, such as "Cue the Rain", https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/If_You_Say_So, "Hey You", "Christmas in New York", among others. The sources and all the information is in the same article, read.
Just to clarify, since not all of us consider it that way.

Probably labeled that way by her fans. Just search "male sex symbols" or "fashion icons" on google images and you won't find a single reference to this guy. It's surprising that Wikipedia allows these lines, with that "neutral point of view" that you claim to have.
They are not accusations of racism, only bullying.

Her awards are subsequently mentioned in the next paragraph:  "...various awards, including a SAG Award and ALMA Award, as well as earning nominations with the rest of the cast for two Grammy Awards and one Brit Award."
I request a new consensus, this photo is superior
Illiteracy? As if she really was.
As I said before, Melissa Benoist did not confirm, she did not even comment on it.
Very unwise to consider an Internet meme as part of her "personal life".
Melissa Benoist did not confirm anything or comment on it.
